reviewText: Enjoyed learning of this people's journey; however I believe that it would have been a more complete production had there been more details of everyday living including contact info. That would have been a nice jester should interested individuals want to go deeper in their own discovery about being an Israelite. I would think in depth sharing of this journey is important to many.
Even though the topic is interesting to an extend it does not really show the kind of life these people live.
It's a really good documentary. Learned alot from it

An inspiring movie about one path taken by a group of people seeking a new and better life!  So glad the film was made when all of the village founders were still alive.  Their character and spirit was captured for all those who want to learn from their journey. What a sensitive and beautiful portrayal!
very different yet very interesting and inspiring to see progress of blacks doing something positive for themselves and others as well wonderful and delightful
